<div class="container section-3">
	<h2 class="text-center">How does it work?</h2>
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-6 col-md-push-6">
			<img src="img/example.png" class="img-responsive" />
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-6 col-md-pull-6">
			<p class="img-desc">
			HookTurns takes the same real-time data you see from other transport applications. But we add crowdsourced information about each tram service's potential to be crowded. The bar beneath each tram's estimated time to arrival indicates the estimated crowd level as advised from fellow commuters, so you can plan ahead to look for alternatives, or wait until the crowd has settled down. You can contribute by rating a tram's crowd level once you see it, and help other commuters in the process.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-6">
			<img src="img/example2.png" class="img-responsive" />
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-6">
			<p class="img-desc">
			We also let you see disruptions formally notified from relevant public transport authorities, or notes of concern from fellow commuters, ranging from minor inconveniences, such as cleanliness or poor driving, or advising others about a disruption not yet passed on formally.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
